<dl id="sa0021bh"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="sa" href="#sa0021bh">SA (VI.A) </a>: <a href="../../FF/fnbs/ssaall.htm#sa0021bh"> 021(bh)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> his breast was broadened:</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">When the answer reached the Wazir, he rejoiced and <mark>his breast was broadened</mark>, for that he was passionately in love with her. He bade set food before all the folk, saying, &ldquo;Eat; this is my bride-feast; for I purpose to go in to the Princess Dunya this night.&rdquo; <small> Richard Burton, &ldquo;Terminal Essay&rdquo; in <a name="RB01" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#RB01"><cite title="source">1000 Nights and 1 Night</cite></a> (Denver, 1919) x.44</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
